
Overview of noun brotherhood

The noun brotherhood has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                    
1. (1) brotherhood -- (the kinship relation between a male offspring and the siblings)
2. (1) brotherhood, fraternity, sodality -- (people engaged in a particular occupation; "the medical fraternity")
3. (1) brotherhood -- (the feeling that men should treat one another like brothers)
4. union, labor union, trade union, trades union, brotherhood -- (an organization of employees formed to bargain with the employer; "you have to join the union in order to get a job")
